title: Microsoft Quarterly Earnings Show Slowest Growth in Five Years
description: The technology giant faced a strong U.S. dollar and weakening demand for personal computers in its latest financial results.

title: Alphabet’s Profit Drops 27 Percent From a Year Earlier
description: Google’s parent company reported earnings that were below analysts’ expectations, bringing in $13.9 billion in profit on $69.1 billion in sales.

title: Russia’s Uunsupported ‘dirty bomb’ claims reverberate in right-wing U.S. communities.
description: Russia’s unsupported claim was portrayed as believable in right-wing American media, and as a warning that could serve to escalate the conflict for Ukraine’s benefit or trigger a world war.

title: Spotify Wants to Get Into Audiobooks but Says Apple Is in the Way
description: Apple has rejected Spotify’s new app three times from its App Store. It is the latest in a series of confrontations between the two companies.

title: GM Reports Increased Profits in Third Quarter Amid High Inflation
description: General Motors sold more cars in the third quarter after struggling with a shortage of computer chips earlier in the year.

title: WhatsApp Is Down in Countries Around the World
description: The messaging app was down on Tuesday morning. WhatsApp said it was working to restore service as quickly as possible.
